	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Mother to Sue Verant</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=567539" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
And now for your daily dose of freaky lawsuits... it appears as if a disgruntled mother, grieving for the loss of her son, will be seeking the heads of Verant Executives for the addictive nature of EverQuest, which she believes to be the primary cause of her son's suicide. 
<p>
<a href="http://www.jsonline.com/news/state/mar02/31536.asp" target="_blank"><b>Click here to read the full article...</b></a>
<p>
Our condolences go out to the mother on her loss.
<p>
On a side note, personally, I think it would be hilarious to see this plastered on all sides of the EverQuest retail boxes:
<p>
<center><img src="http://www.drunkenfriar.com/images/surgeongeneral.gif"></center></blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
