			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hello.  Just afew things I wanted to share about what I thought of the article.  Just some of my opinions and no I don't care if you agree with me; half agree with me; or think I am a sick bastard.  =)  <BR>
<BR>
Quote: <BR>
<BR>
&quot;It's like any other addiction,&quot; Elizabeth Woolley said last week. &quot;Either you die, go insane or you quit. My son died.&quot; <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Hob's Comment: <BR>
<BR>
-I opt for the insanity when I hit level 20, thought I would go beyond the surname. Guess that means anyone playing EQ beyond level 20 is insane since they are not dead or quit playing. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Quote: <BR>
<BR>
She (the mother) has hired an attorney who plans to sue the company in an effort to get warning labels put on the games. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Hob's Comment: <BR>
<BR>
-OMFG. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Quote: <BR>
<BR>
&quot;The manufacturer of EverQuest purposely made it in such a way that it is more intriguing to the addict,&quot; Parker said. &quot;It could be created in a less addictive way, but (that) would be the difference between powdered cocaine and crack cocaine.&quot; <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Hob's Comment: <BR>
<BR>
Well no $*&amp;T they made it intriguing. Why the hell would you pay 13 bucks a month to play something that is boring and pointless? A company won't make any money without customers. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Quote: <BR>
<BR>
&quot;He thought the characters had come out of the game and were chasing him,&quot; Parker said. &quot;He was running through his neighborhood having hallucinations. I can't think of a drug he could have taken where he would have disintegrated in 15 weeks.&quot; <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Hob's Comment: <BR>
<BR>
-OMFG. If someone would actually think the characters would come out of the screen and chase him, well I think the problem goes a little deeper then a video game. I mean my god are people like this Dr. Parker that F%^ing stupid? Looks like any moron can be adoctor, maybe the guy who thought the characters were chasing him would like a shot at being an MD. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Quote: <BR>
<BR>
It may be that the character was slain in combat and Woolley had trouble recovering him. Or, he could have lost a treasured artifact or massive wealth, or been cast out of one of the game's social clubs, called guilds. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Hob's Comment: <BR>
<BR>
-Well I feel his pain if he couldn't get his body. I admit I have killed myself in RL many times and set fire to other people because I couldn't loot my corpse. I could be wrong but I think there are crazy and unstable people everywhere in the world. They may eat a peanut butter sandwich then kill 20 people and then themselves, but I have never seen a warning label on a jar of Jiff. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Quote: <BR>
<BR>
...a negligence action might be won if plaintiffs could successfully argue EverQuest's publishers &quot;should have foreseen an unreasonable risk of harm, that people could potentially hurt themselves. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Hob's Quote: <BR>
<BR>
-People get hurt doing anything. Again I think people are crazy unstable and others just look for an excuse for things they did because they didn't want to take any blame. Just my opinion but it seems that people today are looking for someone to blame for something. Kid shot a teacher, the music made him do it, poor kid it was the music's fault; a guy killed himself, it is the games fault. Anyone who shots someone, that was their action, their choice; some guy who played Everquest who killed himself didn't kill him self because of a game, he killed himself because he wanted to kill himself. I have never be possesed, magicial taken over, or controled by aliens for anything I have done in my life. I have done everything by choice and I believe that everyone has a choice in any matter, other wise we all would have killed ourselves because of Everquest. <BR>
<BR>
-This has just been my opinions. A reflection at how screwed up things are and a time to laugh at ourselves. Yes it is sad the guy killed himself, but warning labels on video games? Yeah ok for violence and ratings ok, but I mean this case here is rediculous. Before you know it you have warnings labels all over the boxes; there won't even be any game pics or quotes from this or that magizine on how cool the game is. All you will have is system requirements, the name and 65 different warnings. <BR>
<BR>
WARNING: CHEWING ON THIS GAME MAY RESULT IN DEATH. <BR>
<BR>
WARNING: SELF PROCREATING WHILE PLAYING THIS GAME MAY CAUSE BLINDNESS. <BR>
<BR>
WARNING: ANY WARNINGS MAY LEAD TO FUTURE WARNINGS ON SEQUELS. <BR>
<BR>
Oh by the way I didn't kill myself and set fire to any other people.... <BR>
<BR>
...this week. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
=)  Anyways just my opinion, like to exercise that illision called freedom of speach and if you don't like it you can log on to A. Ro and kiss my Halfling butt.  =)<BR>
<BR>
Hobbital Ringbearer<BR>
A. Ro<BR>
