			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just gotta say this, I agree that it is not responsible sueing Verant for her sons death.  But I must say, that most of you who have posted, probably do not have children, and even more likely, have never had to bury one.  I myself have niether, but I can imagine that the type of grief that goes along with it makes a person think less realistically.  It surely is none of our jobs to judge this mother, who is to say she was a bad mother?  I mean really, do not jump on the band wagon screaming SHE WAS A HORRIBLE MOTHER! because you dont know that.  This poor guy could have just had an imbalance that we are unaware of, and thus, out of her control.  I agree that it was HE who made the decision to kill himself, but I disagree with you folks who feel it necessary to be rude about how the mother is going about doing this.  Will a game label affect your playing the game?  will it make the game any less enjoyable?  NO!  Allow this to play its course, and perhaps time will see it buried alongside the other situations we have discussed here.  But if one side tries to blow thisout of proportion, surely the other side will match blows. I have not seen any other sights with such bigoted responses going either way for this issue, my advice, leave it be, allow it to blow over.  It is this kind of response the opposition wants, because what other reason woud you want to defend your cause so vehemently, unless there was a chance they could be right.  Allow this to settle down, and watch this not even make the headlines, continue making a big deal about it, and watch every attorney available take Verant and Sony on, just to try and expose something that is not there.  <BR>
Media is what is going to make this big, and this message board is a type of media.  Leave it be, and let the big dogs fight this one, your name calling and finger pointing is not going to make any difference other than to taunt them even more, and make them continue on with this suit.  Money? Posthumous Victory?  whats it matter, allow the mother to grieve, allow them to sue, and just continue to play.  They are not threatening to shut EQ down.  At that time, rise up and make your voice heard, now, sit down, shut up, and level your character.
				</font>
			</td>

